benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: GET /1.0/kb/accounts/{accountId}/emails/{accountEmailId}/auditLogsWithHistory - Retrieve account email audit logs with history by id

covered: Valid Request: TC01, TC15, TC16 cover successful retrieval, ordering and schema conformance for valid parameters.
Empty Response: TC02 and TC18 cover empty-result behavior (returns empty array or 404 depending on state).
Query Parameters: TC10 tests benign extra query parameters handling.
Authorization: TC07 and TC08 cover missing and invalid authentication (401 Unauthorized).

Error Responses: TC03 and TC04 cover 404 for missing account/accountEmailId; TC05 and TC06 cover 400 for invalid ID formats; TC12 and TC09 cover downstream timeout and service-unavailable scenarios (504/503).
Large Result Set / Performance: TC11 exercises large result sets and includes a response-time expectation.
Security: TC13 and TC14 include SQL injection and XSS style inputs and verify validation rejects them.
Regression/Backward compatibility: TC15 and TC16 explicitly validate ordering and schema compatibility.
gaps: Pagination: No scenarios validate pagination, limits, offsets, or server behavior when results are paginated (important given TC11 large dataset).
Caching Behavior: No tests check caching headers (ETag, Cache-Control, Last-Modified) or conditional requests (If-None-Match / 304).
Rate Limiting / Throttling: No tests simulate many rapid requests to verify 429 / rate-limit behavior or backoff handling.
Authorization granularity / Permissions: No tests for 403 Forbidden (valid auth but insufficient permissions / cross-account access).
5xx Server Errors: No explicit tests for 500 Internal Server Error or graceful handling of server-side failures beyond downstream timeouts and 503.
Content Negotiation / Headers: Apart from Content-Type, no tests for Accept header handling or other relevant headers.
Pagination response contract: No verification of pagination metadata (if applicable) or stable ordering across pages.
Validation edge-cases for IDs: While invalid format and malicious inputs are checked, there are no tests for borderline UUID variants (uppercase, braces) or very long path segments.
Rate/Load under large payloads: TC11 checks response time for >1000 items, but there is no stress/load testing or resource-use assertions.
recommendations: Add pagination tests: include scenarios for page size, page number/offset, boundary pages (first, last, beyond-last) and verify ordering/stability across pages.
Add caching/conditional request tests: verify ETag / Last-Modified headers, test If-None-Match returns 304, and ensure Cache-Control directives are present and correct.
Add rate-limiting tests: simulate bursts of requests to confirm expected status (e.g., 429) and retry behavior.
Add authorization-permission tests: validate 403 responses when an authenticated user lacks permission or attempts cross-account access.
Add server-error tests: simulate 500 Internal Server Error and verify client-observable behavior and error messages.
Add content-negotiation tests: vary Accept headers and confirm Content-Type handling and appropriate error responses for unsupported types.
Harden ID validation tests: include variants of UUID formatting and very long/edge-case path segments to ensure robust validation and proper error messages.
Extend performance testing beyond single large-result test: include load tests and verify resource usage and stability under sustained high load.
